VALUES
(41, 13, 19, 29, 2, 2, 2, 'such as was not from the beginning', 'Affliction and Unprecedented Events', 'Both passages emphasize a time of great affliction and darkness that is unparalleled in history. Mark 13:19 speaks of affliction ''such as was not from the beginning,'' while Joel 2:2 describes a day ''there hath not been ever the like.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 19, 40, 24, 21, 21, 'such as was not from the beginning', 'Connection of Great Tribulation', 'Both passages emphasize a time of great affliction or tribulation that is unparalleled in history. They describe this period as one that has not occurred since the beginning of creation.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 19, 27, 9, 26, 26, 'affliction, such as was not from the beginning', 'Affliction and Desolation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize a time of great distress and destruction. Mark 13:19 speaks of unparalleled affliction, while Daniel 9:26 describes desolations determined after the Messiah''s cutting off.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 19, 41, 10, 6, 6, 'from the beginning of the creation', 'Creation and Affliction Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of creation in both passages. Mark 13:19 refers to a time of unprecedented affliction, while Mark 10:6 emphasizes God''s creation of male and female, suggesting a foundational aspect of existence that precedes such affliction.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 19, 42, 21, 22, 24, 'affliction, such as was not from the beginning', 'Connection of Distress and Vengeance', 'Both passages emphasize a time of great distress and affliction. Mark highlights unprecedented affliction, while Luke describes it as days of vengeance and great distress.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 19, 5, 4, 32, 32, 'such as was not from the beginning', 'Affliction and Unprecedented Events', 'Both passages emphasize unprecedented affliction and events since creation. Mark 13:19 speaks of affliction not seen before, while Deuteronomy 4:32 questions if any such great thing has occurred since creation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 20, 40, 24, 22, 22, NULL, 'Connection of Elect and Days Shortened', 'Both passages emphasize that for the elect’s sake, those days shall be shortened to ensure salvation. The similar phrasing in both verses indicates a direct textual parallel regarding the preservation of life during difficult times.', 'parallel', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 20, 23, 65, 8, 9, 'for the elect’s sake', 'Elect and Preservation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the preservation of the elect for their sake. Mark highlights the shortening of days for the elect, while Isaiah speaks of saving a remnant for the servants'' sake.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 20, 38, 13, 8, 9, 'the elect’s sake, whom he hath chosen', 'Refinement and Preservation of the Elect', 'Both passages emphasize the preservation of a remnant during times of trial. Mark speaks of the elect being saved, while Zechariah describes a third part being refined and preserved. This connection highlights God''s protection over those chosen.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 20, 45, 11, 28, 32, 'for the elect’s sake', 'Election and Mercy Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s election and mercy. Both passages emphasize the idea that God acts for the sake of the elect and extends mercy to those who have not believed.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 20, 23, 1, 9, 9, 'the elect’s sake', 'Remnant and Elect Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine preservation in times of judgment. Both passages emphasize that for the sake of a chosen group, God intervenes to prevent total destruction.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 20, 45, 11, 5, 7, 'the elect’s sake', 'Election and Remnant Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of the ''elect'' and ''election.'' Mark highlights God''s action for the elect''s sake, while Romans discusses the remnant according to the election of grace, indicating a divine selection amidst broader circumstances.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 21, 40, 24, 23, 25, NULL, 'Warning Against False Christs', 'Both passages emphasize the warning against false claims of Christ''s presence. They share the phrase ''Lo, here is Christ; or, there'' to highlight the deception that may arise in the last days.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 21, 42, 21, 8, 8, 'believe him not', 'Warnings Against False Christs', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of deception by false claimants of Christ''s identity. They caution believers not to follow those who assert they are Christ, highlighting the importance of discernment in the face of misleading teachings.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 21, 40, 24, 5, 5, 'Lo, here is Christ; or, lo, he is there;', 'Warnings Against False Christs', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of false claims to be Christ. Mark warns against believing such claims, while Matthew notes that many will come in His name, deceiving many.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 21, 5, 13, 1, 3, 'believe him not', 'Warning Against False Prophets', 'This connection highlights the caution against following false prophets in both passages. Mark 13:21 warns believers not to believe claims of Christ''s presence, paralleling Deuteronomy 13:1-3''s admonition against heeding prophets who lead to other gods.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 21, 42, 17, 23, 24, 'believe him not', 'Warnings Against False Claims', 'Both passages emphasize the caution against following false claims about the presence of Christ. They instruct believers not to be misled by those who assert that Christ is present in specific locations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 21, 43, 5, 43, 43, 'believe him not', 'False Messiahs and Reception', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejecting true messengers while accepting false ones. Both passages emphasize the idea of discernment regarding who is truly sent from God.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 22, 40, 24, 24, 24, NULL, 'Connection of False Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the rise of false Christs and false prophets who perform signs and wonders. They warn that these deceptions could mislead even the elect, highlighting a shared theme of caution against false teachings.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 22, 53, 2, 8, 14, 'false Christs and false prophets', 'Connection of False Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of false prophets and deceptive signs. Mark warns of false Christs seducing the elect, while 2 Thessalonians describes the Wicked''s coming with signs and lying wonders. This connection highlights the theme of deception in the end times.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 22, 41, 13, 6, 6, 'false Christs and false prophets', 'Connection of Deception Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the rise of false Christs and prophets who will deceive many. This connection highlights the warning against those claiming to be Christ and the potential to mislead even the elect.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 22, 40, 7, 15, 15, 'false prophets', 'Connection of False Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of false prophets who deceive believers. Mark warns of those who perform signs to seduce, while Matthew describes false prophets as wolves in sheep''s clothing.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 22, 43, 10, 27, 28, 'if it were possible, even the elect', 'Connection of Protection and Guidance', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of divine protection for the faithful. Mark warns of false prophets attempting to mislead, while John assures that the true followers are secure in Christ''s care.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 22, 62, 2, 26, 26, 'to seduce, if it were possible, even the elect', 'Connection of Seduction by False Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seduction by false prophets. Mark warns of those who will attempt to deceive even the elect, while 1 John addresses the issue of those who seduce believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 22, 43, 4, 48, 48, 'signs and wonders', 'Connection of Signs and Wonders', 'Both passages emphasize the role of signs and wonders in belief. Mark warns of false prophets performing signs to deceive, while John highlights the necessity of seeing signs for belief.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 23, 61, 3, 17, 17, 'I have foretold you all things', 'Forewarning and Steadfastness', 'This connection highlights the theme of forewarning in both passages. Mark 13:23 emphasizes being informed of future events, while 2 Peter 3:17 warns believers to remain steadfast against deception, acknowledging their prior knowledge.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 23, 23, 44, 7, 8, 'I have foretold you all things', 'Divine Foreknowledge and Declaration', 'Both passages emphasize God''s foretelling of future events. Mark 13:23''s ''I have foretold you all things'' parallels Isaiah 44:7-8''s declaration of God''s knowledge and proclamation of what is to come.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 23, 41, 13, 5, 5, NULL, 'Warnings Against Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the need for vigilance against deception. Mark 13:5 warns to ''take heed'' to avoid being misled, while Mark 13:23 reassures that all things have been foretold, underscoring the importance of awareness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 23, 42, 21, 8, 8, NULL, 'Warnings Against Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the need for vigilance against deception. Mark warns that he has foretold all things, while Luke specifically cautions against false claims of Christ''s return.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 13, 23, 43, 14, 29, 29, 'I have foretold you all things', 'Foretelling and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the act of foretelling events to strengthen belief. Mark 13:23 states, ''I have foretold you all things,'' while John 14:29 highlights that knowledge of events before they occur is meant to foster belief.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
